qXQ3ZBdwI3GlbR5-eYWqNA
First things first: Saba's does not have the best Mediterranean food in Phoenix. There are just some really awesome Lebanese places in Tempe and elsewhere around the valley, and as I discovered yesterday, we even have some excellent Moroccan food. But Saba's is very, very good. Possibly the best in the Paradise Valley-ish area.  Another thing: if you don't like Saba's because you've had better gyros, or you found your pita sandwich too lackluster, you are an idiot. Not because their sandwiches are good - I don't know if they are, because YOU DON'T GO TO A QUALITY MEDITERRANEAN PLACE TO GET A PITA SANDWICH. There, I said it.  The only places you judge solely based on pita sandwiches are places that primarily serve pita sandwiches.  No, at Saba's, it's the entrees that shine. The lamb kafta, the lamb shank, you know... actual entrees. Their baba gannouj is excellent; I get that every time.  To round out your sides, the grilled veggies are a great choice.  They also have fries with feta cheese and seasonings, but I didn't like those as much.  The mango juice is also a must.  So, to reiterate, Saba's is very, very good - so long as you don't get the same thing that you can get at every dime-a-dozen Mediterranean fast-food place on earth. The best? No, but it owns the neighborhood, as far as this genre is concerned.

