The lady who said the brisket is "tough, flavorless, and dry" is mistaken; she apparently meant to review the paper towels on the tables. The brisket is fantastic.  The pulled pork was a little too juicy for my taste. I prefer my pulled pork not to be steeped in grease, but some may disagree. Tasted OK, but not my favorite pulled pork by any stretch.  The sides were a little pedestrian.  Definitely planning on coming back and trying the other meats, and having more of the paper towels.

